Benoit Coeure, deputy director of
the French Treasury, is the leading candidate to succeed Lorenzo
Bini Smaghi on the executive board of the  European Central Bank ,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, without saying where it
got the information.  Treasury official Ramon Fernandez and  Xavier Musca , an
adviser to President  Nicolas Sarkozy , had been in the running
but were no longer seen as serious candidates, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
